New `eli' Parameter
*******************

   We have added a parameter `-p `dir'' to the `eli' command (*note
Packages in the cache: (sysadmin)Capability.).  Here `dir' is the
absolute path name of a directory containing either a package or a
package collection (*note Package Management: (sysadmin)Packages.).

   An `eli' command may have any number of `-p' parameters, which are
considered in order from left to right.  They are effective only when
the cache specified by the `eli' command does not exist, or when it is
being rebuilt because the `-R' parameter is also given.  In either
case, the package(s) specified are added to the set of packages to be
used in building the cache (*note Cache Management: (sysadmin)Caches.).


