The `installpkg' Product
************************

   The standard Eli packages can be installed in a library that can be
updated without affecting any caches currently being used (*note
Installation: (sysadmin)Install.).  Updates only take effect if a new
cache is created or an existing cache is reset by executing and `eli'
command on that cache with the `-R' parameter.

   We have added the `installpkg' product to allow users to install
additional packages in the standard library or to create their own
libraries (*note Installing additional packages:
(sysadmin)PkgInstall.).  To take advantage of this facility, the
packages must be "versioned" (*note Versioned packages:
(sysadmin)Versioning.).


